📌 Introduction:
This project was completed as part of the Digital Literacy course with the aim of understanding how digital tools can be used effectively in academics and daily online activities. As a student Digital Ambassador, the goal was to explore different aspects of digital literacy such as creating visual content, building an online professional presence, using collaboration tools, practicing coding, and understanding cyber safety.
The project consisted of five tasks, each focusing on a specific module. These tasks included designing an infographic, creating and managing professional profiles on platforms like GitHub and LinkedIn, solving a coding challenge, using Google Forms and Sheets for collaboration, drafting professional emails, and studying a cybercrime scenario through a case study.
Through this project, I was able to gain practical exposure to commonly used digital platforms and develop a better understanding of how to use them responsibly and efficiently in an academic environment.

🎨 Task 1 Write-up

For Task 1, I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva. The purpose of the infographic was to explain what digital literacy means and why it is important for students in today’s digital world. The design includes key points such as safe internet practices, maintaining a professional online presence, and the use of useful digital tools.
While creating the infographic, I focused on keeping the content simple, clear, and visually organized. I used a combination of colors, icons, and short text to make the information easy to read and understand. One challenge I faced was managing all the content within a single page without making it look overcrowded. I had to carefully decide which points were most relevant and arrange them in a clean layout.
This task helped me understand how visual tools can be used to communicate information effectively. It also improved my ability to present ideas in a structured and concise manner using design platforms like Canva.

💼 Task 2 Write-up

In Task 2, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle to build my digital portfolio. Each platform plays a different role in developing a professional online identity.
GitHub is used for storing and sharing code and projects, and it also helps in collaborating with others. I created a profile README that includes my basic details and learning goals. LinkedIn is a professional networking platform where I updated my education details, which helps present my academic background in a structured way. Kaggle is mainly used for learning data science concepts, exploring datasets, and participating in competitions.
Setting up these platforms helped me understand the importance of maintaining a consistent and professional digital presence. These profiles will be useful in the future for internships, projects, and networking opportunities.
Over time, I plan to actively use GitHub to upload projects, LinkedIn for professional connections, and Kaggle to improve my technical and analytical skills.

💻 Task 3 Write-up

In Task 3, I explored coding practice and collaboration tools. I used HackerRank to complete a beginner-level coding challenge, which helped me strengthen my understanding of basic programming concepts and improve problem-solving skills.
Along with this, I created a Google Form consisting of five questions related to digital literacy awareness. The form includes both multiple-choice and short-answer questions. I linked the form to a Google Sheet, which automatically collects and organizes the responses submitted by users.
This task gave me practical exposure to how online platforms can be used for both learning and collaboration. Coding platforms like HackerRank help in improving logical thinking and coding skills, while tools like Google Forms and Sheets are useful for collecting data, conducting quizzes, and managing responses efficiently.
Overall, this task helped me understand how different digital tools can support academic activities and make learning more interactive and organized.

✉️ Task 4 Write-up

This task helped me understand the importance of professional communication and proper email etiquette. Writing formal emails requires clarity, politeness, and a structured format, which is essential in academic and professional environments.
One common issue that can arise due to poor digital communication is sending unclear or unprofessional emails. For example, if a student sends a vague message without a proper subject line or greeting, it may lead to confusion or a delayed response. Such situations can be avoided by following basic email etiquette, such as using a clear subject line, proper greetings, concise content, and a respectful closing.
This task made me realize that effective communication is not just about conveying a message, but also about presenting it in a professional and organized manner. It also highlighted the importance of being mindful while communicating online.

🔐 Task 5 Write-up

While researching cybercrime, I learned about phishing attacks and how commonly they are used to deceive users. What surprised me most was how convincing these fake messages and websites can appear, making it difficult for users to distinguish between real and fraudulent sources.
Earlier, I did not always pay attention to verifying links or checking the authenticity of messages. After completing this task, I understood the importance of being cautious while interacting with unknown emails or websites. One habit I would like to improve is to always verify URLs and avoid clicking on suspicious links without proper confirmation.
This task increased my awareness of online threats and emphasized the need to follow safe browsing practices. It also helped me realize that small precautions can prevent major issues related to cybercrime.

🎯 Conclusion

This project helped me gain practical experience with various digital tools and platforms that are widely used in academics and professional environments. Each task contributed to improving my understanding of digital literacy, online communication, collaboration tools, and cyber safety.
By completing this project, I learned how to create visual content, manage professional profiles, use coding platforms, collaborate using Google tools, and understand cybercrime prevention techniques. These skills are important for students in today’s digital world.
Overall, this project enhanced my confidence in using digital platforms effectively and responsibly, and helped me build a strong foundation for maintaining a professional digital presence in the future.

